IMPORTANT MESSAGE!



COVID-19 Update – April 21, 2020



As we close out the fifth week of school closure, it’s refreshing to hear news from the governor that the daily reports of COVID-19 cases are gradually subsiding. Hopefully, this provides some sense of vindication that the sacrifices you have made are paying dividends.

Based on this past week’s Executive Order, schools will now remain closed through May 15. Despite this news, your son’s learning continues. All classes, including teacher led courses, can now be found on Edgenuity and he should be working on each course for a total of 3 hours per course, per week.

As we continue to navigate through our new normal, please do not hesitate to reach out to your Vertus family if you have questions, or need support. With so many things about the remainder of the school year out of our control we will do the very best we can to help you and your family in any way possible. One of the pillars of our school, “building strong relationships,” has sustained us through all of this, but I am truly looking forward to the day when we can be back in school together. Take care, stay safe, and be healthy!

Julie A. Locey, Principal








